Class NBMatchFilter

  OpenFlow.NBAPI.NBMatchFilter
Direct Known Subclasses:
ControllerContext.CtxNBMatchFilter
public class NBMatchFilter
extends java.lang.Object

OpenFlow context Northbound API packet-in match filter.

An immutable object with respect to packet-in match filter criteria, this object also provides and API for changing the associated auxData component when returned from (allocated by) the ControllerContext addReceiveMessageFilter() methods (when connected, change requests are issued to the server when the setAuxData() methods are called).

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object other_obj)
Is this match filter equal to (strict match) another.

This method compares whether the datapathID, pInReason, and OFMatchPB components are specification-equal with respect to wild-carding (where a wild-carded OFMatchPB field value may be set but is ignored for the comparison). The auxData, has_calls, and other instance members are also ignored for this comparison.

Overrides:
equals in class java.lang.Object

hashCode

public int hashCode()
Attempt to comform to Java required relationship with equals().

Note: It is possible to create two instances of this class for which equals(Object) returns true, but each object has a distinct hashCode() value. The equals(Object) method compares whether the logical OFMatchPB components match with respect to wild-carding, where a wild-carded field value may be set but ignored, whereas this hashCode() function makes use of the OFMatchPB.hashCode() method, which is dependent on all field values, regardless of their relevance to a match.
